sql:
SELECT properties.property_id, property_transactions.transaction_date
FROM properties
JOIN property_transactions ON properties.property_id = property_transactions.property_id;

SELECT property_id, transaction_date
FROM property_records
WHERE transaction_type = 'sale';

SELECT property_id, property_status 
FROM properties 
WHERE property_type_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- '3 ROOM' models refer to a specific type of flat model;
- 'birthplaces' metaphorically refer to the towns where the properties are located;
- 'architects' refers to the names of the flat models in this context;
- 'guardians' metaphorically refers to the owners of the properties;
- 'harvest season of 2014 to 2015' is a metaphorical way to describe the lease period between '2014-08-01' and '2015-07-01'.

sql:
SELECT property_id, block_number, street_name, floor_area_sqm 
FROM properties 
WHERE floor_area_sqm > (SELECT AVG(floor_area_sqm) FROM properties);

external_knowledge:
- "specific type" refers to properties with a property_type_id of 1;
- "acquired in the last year" means the ownership_start_date is greater than '2023-01-01';
- "interacted with such properties more than once" indicates that there are more than one access records related to the property in the access logs.

sql:
SELECT town_name, total_properties, total_occupied_properties
FROM towns
WHERE total_properties > 1000 AND total_occupied_properties < 100;
